cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.OS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about building locality-preserving distributed systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of network delay on response latencies in distributed systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a framework to transform existing distributed algorithms to be locality-preserving. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the performance improvement achieved by the proposed framework. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the overhead of the proposed framework on each physical node.
